<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="629" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[1975,2572,1392,1820]" pageId="30" pageNumber="629">
Taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Winton" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[2282,2408,1471,1505]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="30" pageNumber="629" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="henleyi">G. henleyi</taxonomicName>
is not con- tested, despite lack of molecular data. Its morphological characters were revised by D. M. Lay in 1983 and by I. Ya. Pavlinov and colleagues in 1990. D. L. Harrison and P. J. J. Bates in 1991 accepted two different subspecies on geographical grounds. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="629" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="629" startId="30.[1373,1394,1835,1860]" targetBox="[2318,2322,2861,2886]" targetPageId="30">
<paragraph blockId="30.[1975,2572,1392,1820]" lastBlockId="30.[1369,2577,1835,2886]" pageId="30" pageNumber="629">
Subspecies and Distribution 
<taxonomicName authority="de Winton, 1903" authorityName="Setzer" authorityYear="1958" box="[1373,1752,1835,1860]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="30" pageNumber="629" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="henleyi" subSpecies="henleyi">G.h.henleyideWinton,1903—aridzonesofNAfrica(fromWesternSaharaandMoroccotoEgypt),andSoftheSaharafromSMauritaniaandNSenegaltoNSudan,withanisolatedrecordfromDjibouti.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[1369,2577,1835,2886]" pageId="30" pageNumber="629">
<taxonomicName authority="Bonhote, 1910" authorityName="Bonhote" authorityYear="1910" box="[1373,1739,1953,1978]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="30" pageNumber="629" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="henleyi" subSpecies="mariae">G. h. mariae Bonhote, 1910</taxonomicName>
